Definition: usually followed by `to') strongly opposed
Example: antipathetic to new ideas; averse to taking risks; loath to go on such short notice; clearly indisposed to grant their request
Synonyms: noun, feeling, antipathy, cognition, antipathetical, averse, p, indisposed, loath, loth, usually, followed, by, to, strongly, opposed, new, ideas, taking, risks, go, on, such, short, notice, clearly, grant, their, request
Category: adj.all
